.TH HSH 1 "01-08-2026" "0.2" "Simple Shell" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hsh \- simple command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
\fB hsh \fP is a basic shell version.
It's a simple command interpreter that reads commands from
standard input and executes them.
.br
In interactive mode, it displays a prompt and waits for the user
to enter commands.
.br
In non-interactive mode, it reads commands from standard input.

.SH OPTIONS
\fB hsh \fP doesn't take any options.

.SH COMMAND EXECUTION
\fB hsh \fP executes commands by searching for the executable file in the
directories listed in the PATH environment variable.
.br
If a command contains a slash (/), it is executed directly.

.SH OPERANDS
\fB hsh \fP supports the following operands :
.br
.SS build_path
This function builds a PATH.
.SS execute_command
This function executes the command.
.SS find_command_in_path
This function searches the PATH.
.SS get_path
This function extrates the PATH variable.
.SS split
This function parses the arguments.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
\fB hsh \fP uses the PATH environment variable :
.br
list of folders where executable programmes are located.

.SH EXIT STATUS
\fB hsh \fP returns 0 on success.
.br
If a command cannot be found or executed, a new prompt appears.

.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Execute the shell, execute a command and exit the shell in interactive mode :
$ ./hsh
.br
$ ls
.br
$ ^D

.SS Execute the shell and execute a command in non-intercative mode :
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
.br
$

.SH BUGS
No known bugs.

.SH AUTHORS
